MICROLINK TURNOVER UP 106 PERCENT IN H1 ' 97 . The largest computer producer in the Baltics , Microlink , said on Thursday its net turnover was 82 . 6 million kroons in the first six months of 1997 , up 106 percent compared with the same period last year . The sharp rise stemmed from high demand for its computers in Latvia and Lithuania , it added in a statement . It sold 30 percent of its products in the other Baltic countries . Falling computer prices , which have dropped 13 percent since 1996 , also contributed to the sales increase . Microlink has a 15 . 1 percent market share in the Baltics and the majority of Estonia ' s computer market . - - Eva Palu , Tallinn newsroom , + 372 6209 201 , reuters @ reuters . ee 
